1
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:06,000
What do you mean, a blind date?

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,000
I don't do those things.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,200
Because

4
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,800
blind dates are not destined.

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,058
Remember what I said?

6
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:16,100
The documentary.

7
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:18,100
I told you I'm not going.

8
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,500
Destiny?

9
00:00:48,357 --> 00:00:51,247
Damn, that hurts.

10
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,800
Yes.

11
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,500
That destiny...

12
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,800
I'm about to find mine now.

13
00:01:08,639 --> 00:01:13,075
[Best Mistake]

14
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,400
Just a second!

15
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,200
One sec—

16
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,200
Just a second—

17
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:33,000
Oh? That person...

18
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,100
Why are you standing there?

19
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:38,300
Take off your coat and come up here.

20
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,200
Pardon?

21
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:41,100
Aren't you the model?

22
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:44,700
Oh, is he the model?

23
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:46,600
A model?

24
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:55,167
I see.

25
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,100
I am!

26
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:08,700
I'm the model, Professor.

27
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,800
Hey, you.

28
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,300
What do you think you're doing?

29
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,200
Excuse me.

30
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,300
By any chance,

31
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:35,000
do you have a boyfriend?

32
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,700
Sorry?

33
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:37,800
If I say this,

34
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,900
I'm not sure how you will think of me,

35
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:43,000
but I...

36
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,100
I think we're destined for each other.

37
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,000
Pardon?

38
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:53,400
I'm not a weird person at all.

39
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:57,700
You're just my type.

40
00:03:57,700 --> 00:04:02,100
Can you give me your number?

41
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,400
- Excuse me!
- Yes?

42
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,500
Do you always flirt with someone in this way?

43
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,344
Pardon? What do you mean?

44
00:04:11,344 --> 00:04:12,546
"Do you believe in destiny?"

45
00:04:12,546 --> 00:04:13,600
"Do you know asceticism?"

46
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,200
You're telling such things!

47
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,700
Pardon? No, I'm not like that at all.

48
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:19,263
I don't believe in those things.

49
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,400
I will not give you my personal information,

50
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:25,000
so just leave before I report you.

51
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,800
I, um...

52
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,200
What's with that guy?

53
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,200
I'm sorry!

54
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,600
Who... are you?

55
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,600
I'm the model for today.

56
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,200
I slept in late.

57
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,100
What?

58
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,500
I'm sorry!

59
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,000
I'm very sorry, Professor!

60
00:05:03,938 --> 00:05:06,890
Then who was that guy earlier?

61
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,000
What? Give up what?

62
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,800
I don't have a son like you.

63
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,800
So get out, you punk!

64
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,400
Hi!

65
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,400
Okay. You're still the same.

66
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,700
They're peas.

67
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,636
Green peas.

68
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,100
Light green.

69
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,700
Yeon Du.

70
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:42,937
Kim Yeon Du.

71
00:05:42,937 --> 00:05:44,077
Damnit.

72
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:47,200
Now you think of Squirtle every time you see light green?

73
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,168
What an imagination!

74
00:05:49,168 --> 00:05:50,700
Darn it

75
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,500
What's with him?

76
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,000
He broke up with Yeon Du.

77
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
What?

78
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,330
Why?

79
00:05:57,330 --> 00:05:58,559
What happened?

80
00:05:58,559 --> 00:06:00,764
How would Ji Seong know about it?

81
00:06:00,764 --> 00:06:01,765
He called me out of the blue

82
00:06:01,765 --> 00:06:03,300
and said he broke up with Squirtle.

83
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,348
So I came here, worrying for him,

84
00:06:04,348 --> 00:06:06,516
and he's been drinking for an hour.

85
00:06:06,516 --> 00:06:08,080
I even skipped my class.

86
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:11,000
I skipped training.

87
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,700
Me, either.

88
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,300
I don't know, either.

89
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,500
What do you mean?

90
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,807
What on earth don't you know?

91
00:06:21,807 --> 00:06:23,700
Why we broke up!

92
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:26,100
I don't know why.

93
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,956
We were good together.

94
00:06:27,956 --> 00:06:30,400
We got better in college.

95
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,600
We went out more often

96
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,200
and cheered for each other's school lives.

97
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,615
And we got in touch often.

98
00:06:36,615 --> 00:06:38,400
Hold on.

99
00:06:39,557 --> 00:06:40,969
During that process,

100
00:06:40,969 --> 00:06:42,264
did you make her feel disappointed in any way?

101
00:06:42,264 --> 00:06:43,637
No.

102
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:46,100
I did my best every moment.

103
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:47,644
Even on the day of the cooking contest,

104
00:06:47,644 --> 00:06:48,981
she got into an accident with a motorbike,

105
00:06:48,981 --> 00:06:50,200
so I ran to her in an instant.

106
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,100
Wow!

107
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,900
What a romanticist!

108
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:53,800
I agree.

109
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,700
That was awesome.

110
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:58,495
Then why was I dumped?

111
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:03,000
How long have you been dating?

112
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:07,700
We broke up last week...

113
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,500
So until then,

114
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:12,700
680 days?

115
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:15,800
Then did you celebrate your 666th day anniversary?

116
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,800
No.

117
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,400
That's it!

118
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,400
W-Wait...

119
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,000
Are you supposed to

120
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,000
celebrate the 666th day?

121
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,300
Not even the 600th day?

122
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,419
Of course!

123
00:07:28,419 --> 00:07:29,900
Didn't you celebrate your 22nd day?

124
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:32,200
How could you forget your 666th day?

125
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,600
You deserve to get dumped.

126
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:38,000
What does the 666th day even mean?

127
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,700
What?

128
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:42,000
Um...

129
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
I love you as much as 666!

130
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,044
That doesn't even make sense!

131
00:07:46,044 --> 00:07:47,705
Am I the weird one?

132
00:07:47,705 --> 00:07:49,700
Not you guys?

133
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,000
Then

134
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,800
why else would you have been dumped?

135
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:56,000
There is no other reason except that.

136
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,300
Oh!

137
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:59,600
I think I got it!

138
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,800
Did you...

139
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,400
set the table for her when you guys were eating?

140
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,900
Of course! What do you think I am—

141
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,400
At the time!

142
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:13,000
Did you put a napkin underneath or not?

143
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:17,400
Napkin?

144
00:08:18,339 --> 00:08:19,419
I didn't put it.

145
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:22,300
- That's it!
- That's it!

146
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,007
Do you have to put the napkin underneath?

147
00:08:24,007 --> 00:08:24,923
Of course!

148
00:08:24,923 --> 00:08:27,174
People think hygiene is important.

149
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,600
Hey, that is the basic of basics.

150
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,555
That's right!

151
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,900
Someone Ji Seong knew got dumped for the same reason.

152
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:39,400
Is it really because of that?

153
00:08:42,664 --> 00:08:44,326
By the way,

154
00:08:44,326 --> 00:08:47,100
did you try to win her back?

155
00:08:48,494 --> 00:08:50,133
Yes.

156
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:53,200
I went to her school,

157
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,812
but it was no use.

158
00:08:54,812 --> 00:08:58,304
It's said dating is over, even if one side is done with it.

159
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:00,600
You're just in that situation.

160
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,500
Dating is like that,

161
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,000
but love isn't like that.

162
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,800
If you have feelings for her, then how can it be over?

163
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,000
You still like her very much.

164
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,012
So

165
00:09:13,012 --> 00:09:15,264
go as your heart takes you.

166
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,600
Look at me.

167
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:19,500
I came across the continent to meet Seol.

168
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,900
Come to think of it,

169
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:24,500
how did you come, Ju Ho?

170
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,600
Weren't you going to school in the States?

171
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,000
That's right!

172
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,600
You're a law student at Harvard!

173
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:37,300
How's school? How is it different?

174
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,600
I dropped out.

175
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,800
What?

176
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,200
And got kicked out of home.

177
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,400
Well...

178
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,900
My parents told me if entered college, I could drop out or take time off,

179
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:51,700
but I got kicked out when I dropped out for real.

180
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,300
How about Seol?

181
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,257
Did you tell her you're back?

182
00:09:57,257 --> 00:09:59,585
Not yet.

183
00:09:59,585 --> 00:10:01,103
I'll prepare a fancy surprise

184
00:10:01,103 --> 00:10:03,868
before I go to see her.

185
00:10:03,868 --> 00:10:06,491
So keep it a secret in the meantime.

186
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:10,100
Ji Seong has no one to tell it to.

187
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,800
Why not?

188
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,000
You have Yun Ah Ra.

189
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,200
You're doing it again!

190
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:19,400
Ji Seong and Ah Ra aren't in such a relationship.

191
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,700
Of course,

192
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,900
Ah Ra is Ji Seong's destiny,

193
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:26,706
and Ji Seong wants to follow that fate.

194
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,200
But for Ah Ra,

195
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,600
he decided to go against fate.

196
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,200
We're just friends now.

197
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:39,800
Just... friends.

198
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,786
Sure.

199
00:10:41,786 --> 00:10:44,000
How about you, Seung Hyeon?

200
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,600
Are you dating anyone?

201
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,600
Me?

202
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,300
Yes.

203
00:10:56,513 --> 00:10:57,323
One.

204
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:58,157
Two.

205
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:58,908
One.

206
00:10:58,908 --> 00:10:59,799
Two.

207
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:00,660
One.

208
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,500
Two.

209
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,170
One.

210
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:03,790
Two.

211
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,600
He's good at baseball

212
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:14,603
and good looking, too.

213
00:11:15,972 --> 00:11:19,125
That's not fair, Seung Hyeon.

214
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,442
Phew!

215
00:11:21,442 --> 00:11:23,900
Ten minute break!

216
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,769
They must be done.

217
00:11:32,171 --> 00:11:33,929
Here.

218
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,500
I told you before.

219
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:40,177
I'm not interested in dating.

220
00:11:41,426 --> 00:11:43,002
Even if you're not interested,

221
00:11:43,002 --> 00:11:45,881
you can still receive my gift.

222
00:11:45,881 --> 00:11:48,033
Is this also crossing the line?

223
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:52,286
I'm really not interested in dating

224
00:11:52,286 --> 00:11:55,000
so stop doing this to me

225
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:56,900
and meet someone else.

226
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:58,600
You're the one I like.

227
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,100
What?

228
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,000
So

229
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,100
don't tell me to meet someone else.

230
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,505
Seung Hyeon,

231
00:12:07,505 --> 00:12:10,482
you play baseball hard because you like baseball.

232
00:12:10,482 --> 00:12:12,300
I like you,

233
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:15,000
so I'll keep expressing my feelings.

234
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,600
And this is one of my ways of expressing it.

235
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:25,300
My arms hurts.

236
00:12:30,921 --> 00:12:32,028
The break is over!

237
00:12:32,028 --> 00:12:33,300
Gather up!

238
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:34,531
Your break must be over.

239
00:12:34,531 --> 00:12:36,400
Go on.

240
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,000
Good luck.

241
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,500
Go, Seung Hyeon!

242
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,600
Hmph!

243
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,100
I was wondering where you were.

244
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,632
Seung Hyeon says he hates it.

245
00:12:58,632 --> 00:13:00,000
Why do you keep following him?

246
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,600
Do you have no self-respect?

247
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,500
No!

248
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:06,600
I have no self-respect at all, if it's for the person I like.

249
00:13:07,959 --> 00:13:09,108
Aren't you

250
00:13:09,108 --> 00:13:10,610
a high school senior?

251
00:13:10,610 --> 00:13:11,904
What are you doing here at this hour

252
00:13:11,904 --> 00:13:14,400
instead of going to school?

253
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,200
Don't you need to study?

254
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,758
Today is the school anniversary!

255
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,600
Don't you even know your own school's anniversary?

256
00:13:20,642 --> 00:13:23,586
No, I don't need to know.

257
00:13:23,586 --> 00:13:25,292
Stop being unreasonable

258
00:13:25,292 --> 00:13:27,559
and go study, kid!

259
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,500
Okay?

260
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,900
I was on my way.

261
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:33,772
You don't know anything.

262
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,600
Hmph!

263
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,545
I can say hmph, too!

264
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,696
I can sense

265
00:13:48,696 --> 00:13:50,700
you're all getting tired.

266
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:52,600
All right, all right, I'll finish off.

267
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:56,400
You've learned a really important person in today's lecture.

268
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,912
I was feeling sorry before,

269
00:13:58,912 --> 00:14:01,691
but now we're even.

270
00:14:01,691 --> 00:14:05,850
Next week, regarding this person's view of the basic science,

271
00:14:05,850 --> 00:14:09,400
let's take a look at his research methods and results together.

272
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:12,500
You're all smiles today, Senior.

273
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,200
Oh, right.

274
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:16,800
Wait, no.

275
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,400
Sorry?

276
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:20,500
Nothing.

277
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,500
No, it's nothing.

278
00:14:25,608 --> 00:14:26,659
All right.

279
00:14:26,659 --> 00:14:28,418
This is it for today.

280
00:14:28,418 --> 00:14:30,554
Thank you.

281
00:14:36,157 --> 00:14:37,043
Okay.

282
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:38,600
The lesson is finished.

283
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,400
Starting next week,

284
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,000
you'll be doing a group project.

285
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,928
So you have to get into groups of two,

286
00:14:43,928 --> 00:14:45,136
before you leave class.

287
00:14:45,136 --> 00:14:46,180
Groups of two?

288
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,000
So

289
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,600
before you leave,

290
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:51,000
everyone pick a straw.

291
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:58,200
What number?

292
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,200
